volume.name: Bonanza: Suplemento ao Mundo de Aventuras

description:
The Chronicles of Air Raid Robertson

Our third issue sees another trio of stories for our quixotic aviator. They include...

"Freak Out In A Moonage Daydream" - Air Raid Robertson and Ridley are chosen to provide security for an important diplomatic summit on the moon. Unfortunately for them, this conference is in the crosshairs of T.H.E.E.Y. (Terrorists Harassing Everyone, Especially You!).

"Space Truckin'" - A badly-needed vacation for our heroes is interrupted once a UFO transporting intergalactic zoo animals crashes on Earth. It's up to Robertson and Ridley to stem the onslaught of these invasive species before it's too late.

"Close Your Eyes And Trust In Me" - Hell's worst succubus is about to be demoted to shoveling feces on the flatterers in the eighth circle. Her only way out of this dismal, scatological fate is to somehow corrupt the soul of one Air Raid Robertson.
name: Freak Out In A Moonage Daydream; Space Truckin'; Close Your Eyes And Trust In Me

description:
Blue Collar

Five years ago a serial killer emerged in California, murdering women and staging them in a very specific manner. He signed his crimes with a smiley face drawn with the blood of his victims. The press dubbed him Red Smile. Brian Warner is the lead investigator in the case and spent the last five years hunting the killer. In retaliation for challenging him in a radio interview, Red Smile returned after a three year hiatus to kill again. To further prove his point, he killed Brian's family, only for Brian to return home to find them...
name: Blue Collar

description:
The Case of the King's Nicked Kitsch

You can pick your friends but you can't pick your family or the murdered freelancer you accidentally raised from the dead. When Ira Smith's brother loses a hideous national treasure, it's up to Ira and Rabbit to bring the painting back, safe and scandal-free.
name: The Case of the King's Nicked Kitsch

description: Robyn must journey through the Center of the Earth to find a crystal that will reverse time.

Volume 2: Gamemaster's Guide

Role-Players, not Role Models.

The continuing adventures of Fili (a Fighter), and Noli (a Wizard), in high fantasy hubris and idiocy.

This collection of comic strips first appeared online at favouritecrayon.co.uk, and is packed full of #MMO #RPG #metahumour.
name: Volume 2: Gamemaster's Guide

volume.name: Experience the Magic of the Legend!

description: Just another typical day in Brightstone City for The Gamma Gals, until a mysterious new hero calling himself "Zero G" makes his explosive debut! Who is Zero G? Is Brightstone City ready to handle four superheroes?

Excursion

The beasts are starting to become more cautious about who they attack, but that only serves to worry the survivors. As the monsters start to reveal a side of themselves so far unseen, Elizabeth discovers that someone within the Hamilton household knows her secret and will reveal it unless they get what they want from her.
name: Excursion

description:
Birth of Venus Part 2

Heroes Haven issue 3 brings you deeper into the Venus saga and her historic tragedy that solidified her pain, anguish, and motivation to avenge this mysterious cult of evil soldiers.
name: Birth of Venus Part Two

description:
The Cold War Pt.2

The Lightspeed Enforcers make their way out into Tetro City to stop Cryogen from her freezing frenzy. However Cryogen is not alone. Can the team shut her down and bring peace back to the city?
name: The Cold War Pt.2

description:
Dyme A Dozen

Lou takes the crew to the planet Kromos for some R&R, where a watering hole known as the Dyme Bar holds a vital clue to Lou's past... and trouble for his present.
name: Dyme A Dozen

description:
Cottonmouth Strikes!!!

Electrolyte meets his biggest nemesis in Megalopolis-- Cottonmouth!
name: Cottonmouth Strikes!!!

volume.name: The Misadventures of Electrolyte and The Justice Purveyors

description:
Enter the Mucho part 3: Of Cods and Monsters

Mucho Man and Magnanimous rush to Tokyo. Can they get there in time to stop The Red Herring? Can they save Japan's Mega-Hero, The Perfect Citizen?

In this Issue:

Who is Super Sexy School Girl XXIII?

The Burro busts loose!

Mucho Man nearly pukes!!

Refrigerators!!!
name: Enter the Mucho Part 3: Of Cods and Monsters

description:
Reap the Whirlwind

With Agent down, Counter has the advantage.
name: Reap the Whirlwind

description:
The Fan Service 5

Meet the newest crime fighters in town! Sure they may not be on parr with the New 52, but maybe if we take a look, something cool will happen... OK maybe not.
name: The Fan Service 5

description: Husband & Wife are reunited. But you don't want a family reunion like THIS one.

Youthful Attack

Youthful Attack is the war comic to end all war comics. A break in the line. A dive headfirst into the heart of an explosion. A landscape that doesn't care. The end of the line.
name: Youthful Attack

description: When kittens assemble into a... fureightening... monster powered by cosmic alchemy and teen angst, it's up to the Task Force Rad Squad team to, I dunno, figure it out heroically. They're smart kids. I'm sure they'll be fine!
Beta wraps up her trip to San Imperial as Bryce takes a quick one of his own.
name: Chapter Three

description:
Transmissions from the Machine World

Somewhere buried amongst the stars is a world inhabited only by machines. Day in and day out the same mechanical processes play and repeat. That is until two travellers arrive.

A surveyor from a galactic organization comes to document this world for the universe at large.

A lost woman appears from nowhere. And all she wants is to go home.

Between the two of them, the Machine World will be irrevocably changed.
name: Transmissions From the Machine World

description:
Anne and "vine boy" embark on a rescue mission which forces them to detour from their planned escape route... and venture deeper into unmapped territory.

VINE is a new comic series in the Tarzan/Indiana Jones tradition of exotic action adventure, with an added dose of Tolkienesque fantasy and romance!
The Goats take their destruction worldwide!
This issue collects the first seven Tom Thumbnail micro-comics, printed in tiny booklets which are very popular at comics conventions.
name: The Tom Thumbnail Micro-Comics Collection

description: A down-on-his-luck former superhero is confronted by his estranged daughter as they come to terms with one another and the events that drove a wedge between them years ago.

On Who We Are

A brief intro to the angelic support available to all of mankind. A graphic novel meant to teach people the importance of angelic help and support.
name: On Who We Are

description: Kara is alone. Her only solace is hiding in the wilderness of Eden Park. But the park is not what it seems. Druids, monsters, and fairies lurk just beyond the human gaze. This place has become their sanctuary. There is a silent truce between the magical and mortal worlds. That careful balance is destroyed when a new creature arrives, with a terrible agenda.
Colin Hall goes in search of answers for one of the 21st Century's most puzzling unsolved mysteries.
name: The Paris and M6 Crashes

description:
This compilation reprints the first 2 sold-out parts of Dumb in a single book. Dumb has been nominated for both a Doug Wright Award and an Ignatz Award.

Dumb #1 introduces Georgia in her natural vocally abundant state: working, socializing, volunteering at a bike co-op, going out, all as the pain (represented by stars) interferes more and more. A diagnosis is given, but she is left with little more. Includes an introduction written by Madeleine Palmer, Georgia's voice coach.

Dumb #2 shows the aftermath of diagnosis, the gathering of information, and the trauma of change. An internal battle is waged in images on the page. Includes an an introduction written by Natalie Zina Walschots, a music writer specializing in metal, as well as "Aftermath" and "Splitting."

Innocents have been turning up dead in the West Virginian wilderness for decades, all crushed by fallen trees and decapitated. Was it an act of God or a murderous beaver on the prowl? It’s up to forest rangers Fred and Randall, as well as television personality Infomercial Dan, to stop the insatiable killing machine stalking Big Hole State Park before it can strike again.

volume.name: If You Die In The Woods, Does Anybody Care?

description:
Life & death in paradise part one

Welcome to Barbados 2015, with the introduction of casinos in the 1990's Barbados was catapulted to one of the world's prime destinations. Due to the increasing popularity of beach front property on the island in 1998, developers took it a step further and began construction of the Caribbean's first manmade islands. The 'New Pelican Isles' were completed in 2008 and were home to some of the best golf courses, beach front villas and hotel casinos in the Caribbean. This glitz and glamour also brought a dark side, creating a deep dark underworld which fueled the luxurious lifestyle of the super rich with drugs, sex and other vices.

You follow the lives of Keith, Dwayne, Jason and Denise as they are all caught in the middle of this light and dark world, where things are not so back and white.
name: Part One

description: A collection of modern stories with their roots in traditional tales and myths - from Australia, North Africa, Ireland, China, Tibet and elsewhere.

The Reunion

A Celestial Warlord has landed on a new world, curious of the inhabitants and the competition they may bring him. The world's heroes gather to confront this possible threat.
name: The Reunion

description: TO A PULP is a 13 page comic revolving around a murder mystery. The last two surviving members of a pantheon of superheroes work together to solve it.

Yo, Miss: A Graphic Look at High School takes the reader inside Wildcat Academy, a second chance high school in New York City where all the students are considered at-risk. Through strong and revealing black and white images, Wilde tells the story of "eight students who are trying to get that ticket to the middle class-a high school diploma." Whether they succeed or not has as much to do with what happens outside the classroom as in, and the value of perseverance is matched by the power of a second chance. It is a story that shows these teens in all their beauty, intelligence, suffering, humor, and humanity (and also when they are really pains in the behind.) A view from the trenches of public education, Yo, Miss challenges preconceptions about who these kids are, and what is needed to help them graduate.

volume.name: Yo, Miss: A Graphic Look At High School
